Context-only patch. The academicpages `_layouts/single.html` has a block
that prints the post meta (date + read time). Drop the view-count include
next to read-time. Exact surrounding lines will vary by theme version —
search for `read-time.html` in your single.html and add the new line
immediately after it, inside the same `<p class="page__meta">` (or
equivalent) block.

--- a/_layouts/single.html
+++ b/_layouts/single.html
@@   around the read-time include   @@
     {% if page.read_time %}
       <span class="page__meta-sep"> · </span>
       {% include read-time.html %}
     {% endif %}
+    {% if site.goatcounter.code %}
+      <span class="page__meta-sep"> · </span>
+      {% include view-count.html %}
+    {% endif %}
   </p>

Notes:
  - If your single.html doesn't already have a `page__meta` block, you
    can put `{% include view-count.html %}` anywhere in the post header
    area. The include renders an inline `<span>`, so it composes with
    existing layout flow.
  - The `if site.goatcounter.code` guard keeps the layout clean until
    you've actually configured GoatCounter — no broken fragment appears
    before setup.
